categories.name: Gap
categories.description: The container-gap is mapped under Theme Styles > Element Section, while the content-gap is used in both the default Container and Block settings.

categories.name: Typography
categories.description: The following variables control heading and text sizes across your entire website, and are mapped under Theme Styles > Typography.

categories.name: Box Shadow
categories.description: The following values can be used within any Box-Shadow modal by navigating to Color > Raw.

categories.name: Button
categories.description: The following variables are shared across all button variants and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Style - Default.

categories.name: Button - Primary
categories.description: The following variables define the primary buttons colors and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Style - Primary.

categories.name: Button - Secondary
categories.description: The following variables define the secondary buttons colors and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Style - Secondary.

categories.name: Button - Light
categories.description: The following variables define the light buttons colors and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Style - Light.

categories.name: Button - Dark
categories.description: The following variables define the dark buttons colors and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Style - Dark.

categories.name: Button - Sizes
categories.description: The following variables define the small buttons sizes and are mapped under Theme Styles > Elements - Button > Sizes.

categories.name: Links
categories.description: The following variables define your links colors and are mapped under Theme Styles > Links > Typography.

categories.name: A11y
categories.description: The focus-color and focus-width are mapped in Theme Styles > Typography > Focus Outline, while the focus-offset is used in the global file in Advanced CSS.
